      • mount

        public java.lang.Boolean mount(java.lang.String aDevice,
                      java.lang.String aLocation,
                      java.lang.String aFstype,

        Mount a device to a location

        If the both the device and location are directories, then the method will invoke the "--bind" option. In these cases, both aFstype and aOptions are ignored

        Parameters:

        aLocation - Mount location
        aFstype - File System Type
        aOptions - Mount options
        Returns:
        True if mount was successful

      • statMount

        public MountStat statMount(java.lang.String aLocation)
        Get stat on a device, file or location

        This cannot be used to check whether a location is mounted or not. What this do, is searches for the nearest location in /proc/mounts and return the located part. So if you have a mounted file system on /data, and you stat /data/property/file, then you will get mount stat on /data.

        Parameters:
        aLocation - Device, file, location
        Returns:
        The stat on the nearest match from /proc/mounts
